# Force LF line endings on text files under src/ so tooling (Biome, Node, etc.)
# behaves the same on Windows, macOS, and Linux checkouts. The leading `/` makes
# the pattern relative to the repo root.
#
# `text=auto` lets Git auto-detect text vs binary; `eol=lf` normalizes text
# files to LF on checkout. Binary assets in vosk/, vosk-model/, etc. are
# unaffected because Git won't apply text rules to detected-binary files.
/src/**    text=auto eol=lf
